<HEADLINE> Avalanche 5, Kings 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Dave Reid had a goal and an assist and Joe Sakic
added a goal as the Colorado Avalanche beat the Los Angeles Kings
5-1 Saturday night in a preseason matchup.
</P>
<P>
   Patrick Roy stopped 26 shots. Shjon Podein, Joe Sakic, Matthew
Scorsune and Alexander Riazantsev added goals for Avalanche.
</P>
<P>
   Jere Karalahti got a late power-play goal for the Kings, who
were 1-of-9 on the power play and failed to convert a two-man
advantage.
</P>
<P>
   Podein opened the scoring at 4:18 of the first period. Power
play goals by Sakic, at 12:25, and Scorsune, at 19:28, increased
Colorado's lead to 3-0 after one period. Goals by Reid and
Riazantsev gave Colorado a 4-0 edge after two periods.
</P>
</TEXT>
