<HEADLINE> Baseball: Cuba 16, South Africa 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BLACKTOWN, Australia (AP) -- Two-time defending gold medalist
Cuba made a dominating start in Olympic baseball as three pitchers
combined on a no-hitter in a 16-rout of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
   The Cubans pounded 18 hits Sunday (Saturday night EDT).
</P>
<P>
   Norge Luis Vera pitched the first five innings of the game,
which was stopped after seven innings due to the mercy rule. He
struck out six.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Ariel Contreras and Maels Rodriguez pitched one inning each
for Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   None of the pitchers allowed a walk; only a late error by third
baseman Gabriel Pierre prevented a perfect game.
</P>
<P>
   Antonio Pacheco had three hits and three RBIs. Miguel Caldes had
four hits and Antonio Scull drove in three runs for the Cubans.
</P>
</TEXT>
