<HEADLINE> Wizards 1, Rapids 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Miklos Molnar scored in the 18th minute
as the Kansas City Wizards opened the MLS playoffs with a 1-0
victory over the Colorado Rapids.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City earned three points in the quarterfinal series,
which resumes Wednesday night at Colorado. Game 3, if necessary,
will be next Sunday at Kansas City. The first team to five points
wins the series.
</P>
<P>
   Molnar scored off an assist from Preki, heading the ball past
Colorado goalkeeper David Kramer. It was Molnar's fourth goal in as
many games since returning from injury.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado came close to sending the match to overtime when Paul
Bravo took a shot from outside the box. Junior Agogo redirected the
shot to the far post where Tony Meola made a spectacular diving
save, trapping the ball against the goalpost just before it crossed
the goal line.
</P>
<P>
   The shutout was Meola's first in the postseason after recording
a record-breaking 16 during the regular season.
</P>
</TEXT>
