<HEADLINE> Carolina 5, Tampa Bay 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ESTERO, Fla. (AP) -- Kevin Hatcher had two power-play goals and
an assist as the Carolina Hurricanes defeated Tampa Bay 5-4 in the
preseason opener for both teams Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Wayne Primeau led the Lightning with two goals.
</P>
<P>
   The teams are scheduled to play again Sunday night in Tampa, but
due to Hurricane Gordon, that game could be postponed. Sunday's
baseball game between the Tampa Bay Devil Rays and Oakland
Athletics has been postponed.
</P>
<P>
   Hatcher, signed as a free agent in the offseason, scored the
game-winner, a power-play goal at 12:10 of the third.
</P>
<P>
   Sandis Ozolinsh, making his debut for Carolina after being
acquired in an offseason trade with Colorado, had a goal and three
assists, and Ron Francis had a goal and two assists for the
Hurricanes.
</P>
<P>
   Bates Battiglia also scored for Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan Johnson and Alexander Kharitonov had the other Tampa Bay
goals.
</P>
