<HEADLINE> Volleyball: Italy 3, South Korea 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- World champion Italy was tested early
but earned a 27-25, 25-23, 25-18 victory over South Korea in the
first round of Olympic men's volleyball.
</P>
<P>
   Italian star Andrea Sartoretti had 15 kills, and Alessandro Fei
added four blocks.
</P>
<P>
   Italy has been the world's dominant team for the past decade,
but still is looking for its first Olympic gold medal. The team
finished a disappointing fifth at the 1992 Games and won silver in
'96.
</P>
<P>
   The Italians committed 24 errors in the match, struggling to get
past South Korea in the first two sets. Slowly, Italy began to get
its offense and blocking going.
</P>
<P>
   South Korean hitter Shin Jin-sik had 18 kills.
</P>
<P>
   Tenth-ranked South Korea, which has participated in all but one
Olympics since volleyball was added in 1964, still is looking for
its first medal.
</P>
</TEXT>
