<HEADLINE> Softball: China 5, Italy 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BLACKTOWN, Australia (AP) -- Wang Ying and Tao Hua each had two
hits on Sunday as China took advantage of Italy's four errors for a
5-0 victory in the preliminary round of the Olympic softball
tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Wang had an RBI double to score Tao in the fourth inning, then
scored on a passed ball to make it 2-0. China, the silver medalist
in the inaugural Olympic softball tournament in 1996, scored three
more runs in the fifth inning, when Italy had two more errors.
</P>
<P>
   Wang Lihong allowed two hits over five innings, striking out
six. Zhang Yanquing pitched the final two innings for China.
</P>
<P>
   Italy's Susan Bugliarello gave up four earned runs on six hits
and a walk.
</P>
