<HEADLINE> Sharks 2, Ducks 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Unrestricted free-agent Tony Granato
scored a goal and Vincent Damphousse added two assists as the San
Jose Sharks beat the Anaheim Mighty Ducks 2-1 in a preseason
matchup on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   San Jose goalie Miikka Kiprusoff made 25 saves in his first NHL
start.
</P>
<P>
   Granato's goal came at 15:37 in the first period off a feed from
Jeff Friesen. Niklas Sundstrom added a power-play goal at 3:44 in
the second.
</P>
<P>
   Chris O'Sullivan scored at 18:53 of the third period as the
Ducks avoided the shutout.
</P>
