<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Gymnast Takes Scary Fall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Hungary's only Olympic female gymnast
fell off the uneven bars and landed on the mat in a crumpled heap,
sending a scare throughout the SuperDome on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Adrienn Nyeste was shaken by the fall, but otherwise uninjured,
according to Dr. Eva Martos, the team doctor, who said the gymnast
would be examined again later. Nyeste skipped her last event.
</P>
<P>
   Nyeste, who lists the bars as her favorite event, was getting
ready to do her dismount during the preliminary competition. After
a couple of full-body swings to build momentum, she put her feet on
the bars so she could launch herself into the air.
</P>
<P>
   But her fingers slipped and, with her body already below the
higher bar, she went hurtling face-first toward the ground. She
broke her fall with her knees, but her chest and head still slammed
into a solid mat that is beyond the softer landing area. The crowd
gasped as she hit the ground.
</P>
<P>
   Nyeste lay still for several minutes, her arms at awkward
angles. Her coach and trainers rushed onto the floor, and she
finally sat up a few minutes later.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd applauded and she gave a weak wave.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
