<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.C. Crash Victims Were Family  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   STATESVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Five people killed when a
tractor-trailer slammed into the rear of their minivan were members
of the same North Carolina family, authorities said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Victims were identified as Mickey D. Blackburn, 47, of
Boonville; his wife, Christine Kimmer Blackburn, 38, and children
Mikki Blackburn, 2, Bobbi Kimmer, 4, and Destiny Kimmer, 5.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses said the burning minivan was lodged beneath the
tractor-trailer after Friday's crash on Interstate 77 about five
miles north of Statesville.
</P>
<P>
   Charges were expected to be filed against the truck driver, who
suffered minor injuries, the Highway Patrol said.
</P>
<P>
   ''He just came up on that traffic and wasn't paying attention,''
Sgt. Rick Barrett said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident set off a chain of collisions involving three other
cars. A passenger in one car was seriously injured.
</P>
</TEXT>
