<HEADLINE> Schumer says heating oil prices could double  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Sen. Charles Schumer said Sunday that home
heating oil prices could nearly double this winter unless more oil
is supplied to the market.
</P>
<P>
   At a Manhattan news conference, Schumer urged New Yorkers to
fill their residential tanks now to avoid expected price increases
this winter.
</P>
<P>
   Consumers could pay as much as $2.28 per gallon for home heating
oil compared to last year's $1.31 per gallon average price, Schumer
said.
</P>
<P>
