<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Bus Plunges Into River  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- A passenger bus plunged off a ferry into a river
in central Russia on Sunday, killing 13 people, emergency officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   The bus, traveling a standard route from the regional capital
Kazan to the town of Bazarniye Mataki, had just driven onto the
ferry's deck when it rolled into the Kama River, said Sergei
Klevakin, chief spokesman for the Emergencies Ministry branch in
the province of Tatarstan.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the accident was unclear.
</P>
<P>
   Rescuers saved the bus driver and one passenger, but all the
others aboard were killed, Klevakin said. He had no details about
the victims.
</P>
</TEXT>
