<HEADLINE> Domingo To Skip Wagner Festival  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MUNICH, Germany (AP) -- Placido Domingo says he'll skip the
world-renowned Wagner festival in Bayreuth next year after clashing
with the composer's grandson.
</P>
<P>
   The star tenor told the Sept. 18 edition of Focus magazine that
he had other obligations that conflicted with director Wolfgang
Wagner's rehearsal schedule for ''Die Walkuere'' next June.
</P>
<P>
   ''Unfortunately it was not possible to find a compromise on the
rehearsal dates with Mr. Wagner,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Domingo is the second star to call it quits at Bayreuth. Soprano
Waltraud Meier announced last month that she would not appear in
2001, accusing Wagner of being inflexible in scheduling rehearsals
as well.
</P>
</TEXT>
