<HEADLINE> Police Fire into Riot killing 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- Police fired at mobs of rival political
groups during municipal elections in a western Indian state Sunday,
leaving seven people dead, a domestic news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
   Eight people were injured in stabbing and other incidents of
violence during the clashes between political activists, Press
Trust of India reported. The news agency did not identify the rival
parties.
</P>
<P>
   Police in Ahmedabad in Gujarat state fired at the rioters after
tear gas shells failed to disperse them, PTI said. Three people
were killed on the spot and four died of bullet wounds in a
hospital, it reported.
</P>
<P>
   The clashes occurred after members of rival political parties
argued over balloting in some booths in Ahmedabad, one of the main
trading centers in the state. Authorities imposed a curfew in the
worst-affected areas and polling was suspended in dozens of booths.
</P>
<P>
   Few other details were immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
