<HEADLINE> Police seize 58 pounds of marijuana at airport  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   COLONIE, N.Y. (AP) - A California woman was arrested after
police discovered 58 pounds of tightly compressed marijuana hidden
in luggage and wrapped in cellophane, dryer sheets, ammonia-soaked
towels and Cajun spices.
</P>
<P>
   None of the efforts to mask the drug's odor worked, as police
dogs sniffed out the marijuana in 25-year-old Myeshia Dixon's
luggage Saturday. Police were tipped off by California police that
Dixon was headed to Albany from Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   The marijuana had a street value of $280,000.
</P>
<P>
   Dixon, of San Diego, brought the luggage out to a waiting car
where police arrested her and two others. Jeanine Carpenter, 26,
and Alford Brown, 29, both of Poughkeepsie, were found with a small
amount of marijuana charged with unlawful possession of marijuana,
a violation.
</P>
<P>
   Dixon was charged with felony first-degree criminal possession
of marijuana, and second-degree criminal impersonation, a
misdemeanor.
</P>
<P>
   Dixon purchased the plane ticket under an alias and had a forged
identification card bearing that name.
</P>
