<HEADLINE> Croatia 3, China 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Barbara Jelic blasted 40 kills as
Croatia handed China its second straight surprising loss, dropping
the 1996 silver medalists to 0-2 in women's Olympic volleyball
qualifying.
</P>
<P>
   The Croatians have only two real threats on offense, Jelic and
Natasa Leto, but they were more than enough to give the Chinese
fits.
</P>
<P>
   Croatia (2-0) won the first game 25-23, then dropped the second
28-26 before cruising in the final two frames 25-20 and 25-15
Monday (Sunday night EDT).
</P>
<P>
   The shot of the match, replayed over and over on the venue
televisions, was a blast by Leto that drilled Chinese back-row
player Li Yan square on the left cheek.
</P>
<P>
   Croatian blockers Biljana Gligorovic and Beti Rimac stuffed Sun
for the game-winning point.
</P>
<P>
   The loss was potentially devastating for China, which is ranked
fourth in the world and was expected to contend for another podium
finish. Instead, the Chinese looked awful in a 3-1 defeat to the
United States in the opener, and couldn't find any way to stop the
6-foot-4 Jelic.
</P>
<P>
   Croatia barely won the first game and had a great shot at taking
a 2-0 lead when Jelic smashed two straight balls to give her team a
26-25 edge. Needing to win by two, the Chinese reeled off three
straight points, starting with a kill by Sun Yue, after her
teammates saved a shot by Jelic.
</P>
<P>
   A service winner and another kill by Sun handed China the 28-26
victory.
</P>
<P>
   Leto added 16 kills for Croatia, which is making its first
Olympic appearance.
</P>
<P>
   Sun had 15 kills, but failed to convert on her other 24
attempts.
</P>
</TEXT>
